# Retail Banking Customer Segmentation & Predictive Targeting

## Overview
Analyzed a real bank marketing dataset to identify which customers are most 
likely to subscribe to a savings product. Built a logistic regression model 
to predict subscription probability and optimize marketing ROI.

## Business Problem
Which customers should a bank target to maximize marketing conversion rates 
and return on investment?

## Tools & Technologies
- Python, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Seaborn, Matplotlib
- Logistic Regression, One-Hot Encoding
- Exploratory Data Analysis

## Key Findings
- Customers aged 60+ with high account balances had the highest conversion rates
- Cellular contact methods outperformed other channels
- Repeated contacts reduced conversion — diminishing returns after 3 contacts

